The White House Office of National Drug Control Policy (ONDCP) has released its Performance Reporting System, which outlines the goals and objectives for the National Drug Control Strategy. The system includes two- and five-year targets and metrics for tracking progress in achieving these goals. The ONDCP Director, James Carroll, highlighted President Trump's commitment to addressing the addiction crisis and the whole-of-government approach taken by the Administration. The ONDCP has established nine goals with quantifiable and measurable objectives to be achieved by 2022. The Performance Reporting System can be accessed through the provided link.